seemed different <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX> was that he also seemed far more present and charismatic
than usual, as he hopped discursively from observations on globalization to
stories about his childhood in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Missouri</ENAMEX> to jokes about <ENAMEX TYPE="GAME">basketball</ENAMEX> to his
substantive proposal of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the day</TIMEX>, which was a plan to eliminate <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$10 billion</NUMEX> a
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">year</TIMEX> in corporate tax subsidies.

            The other thing that struck me about <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bradley</ENAMEX>'s performance was the somewhat
inconsistent quality of what one <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">journalist</ENAMEX> recently described as his streak of
