hooey, as when he answered <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">critics</ENAMEX> of his proposals to end child poverty and
extend health insurance to all by repeating the mantra that "in a world of new
possibilities guided by goodness, we can." Beware of policy proposals that
include a change in human nature as one of their essential requirements. There
was more of this kind of thing in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">yesterday</TIMEX>'s address on "<ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">America</ENAMEX> in the New
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Millennium</ENAMEX>," which I read but did not hear him deliver. "Some <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> say we
can never achieve our special destiny," <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bradley</ENAMEX> concluded. "But I say, in a
