<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">asking Bradley</ENAMEX> what that was supposed to mean. What is our "special destiny"
and who are the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> who say we can never achieve it? <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bradley</ENAMEX> actually filled
out the clich√© rather convincingly. "I think that our special destiny is to
lead the world by the power of our example as a pluralistic democracy and a
growing economy and to do so in a way that is consistent with the promise of
the <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Declaration</ENAMEX>," he said. And who disagrees with that view? "<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">People</ENAMEX> who get
caught up in the current moment and don't have a longer view of our history and
our potential," <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bradley</ENAMEX> said. "I could put a number of the <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Republicans</ENAMEX> in
